tachyon.replay

Class ReplayCache<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • tachyon.replay.ReplayCache<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of value returned by this cache

    public final class ReplayCache<V>
extends Object
    An RPC cache which uses RPC keys to avoid repeating non-idempotent RPCs due to retries. Whenever a ReplayCache.ReplayCallable is run via this class, the RPC key and return value for the ReplayCache.ReplayCallable are remembered so that if the RPC key is replayed while the key is still in the cache, the return value can be immediately returned without executing the ReplayCache.ReplayCallable. For RPCs which may throw IOException, use ReplayCache.ReplayCallableThrowsIOException. Example usage:
     
 private final Cache<String, Long> cache = ReplayCache.newInstance();
 ...
 public long myRpc(final boolean val1, final int val2, String key) throws TachyonTException {
   return mCache.run(key, new ReplayCallable<Long>() {
     &#64;Override
     public Long call() throws TachyonException {
       return rpcWhichCanThrowTachyonException(val1, val2);
     }
   });
 }

      • run

        public V run(String key,
             ReplayCache.ReplayCallable<V> replayCallable)
      throws TachyonTException
        Handles the replay logic for the given RPC handler. The provided key is used to manage replays by returning their previous return value instead of re-executing the RPC handler. This is necessary when the RPC is non-idempotent.
        Parameters:
        key - the key for the RPC
        replayCallable - the handler logic for the RPC
        Returns:
        the result of executing replayCallable, or the cached value from a previous invocation
        Throws:
        TachyonTException - when TachyonException is thrown by the handler call
